# Dark Mode

Dark mode should feel like a **softer clinical workspace** — not a black canvas with floating cards. The failure mode is stacking `neutral-950` page backgrounds with `neutral-900` / `neutral-800` panels until the UI feels heavy, flat, and cold.

## Principles

- **Canvas vs inset** — application canvas uses `--pvc-color-surface` (`neutral-900`). Deeper blacks are for **inset dense regions** (data grid body), not full-page shells.
- **Layered surfaces** — each step (surface → muted → raised) must be distinguishable at a glance.
- **Visible structure** — borders, dividers, and table rules stay crisp; do not compensate for low contrast with glow or blur.
- **Readable muted text** — especially in grids, forms, and helper copy (`--pvc-color-text-muted` on `--pvc-color-surface-muted`).
- **Confident accents** — foreground accents lighten; solid button fills stay saturated.
- **Same geometry as light mode** — radius, grid alignment, and divider logic do not change between modes.
- **No decorative gradients** — richness comes from structure, not atmosphere.

## Surface Stack

Application-level dark tokens (from `pathogen.tailwind.css`):

```css
.dark {
  --pvc-color-surface: var(--color-neutral-900);
  --pvc-color-surface-muted: var(--color-neutral-800);
  --pvc-color-surface-raised: color-mix(in oklab, var(--color-neutral-800) 82%, white);
  --pvc-color-border: var(--color-neutral-700);
  --pvc-color-border-strong: var(--color-neutral-600);
  --pvc-color-text: var(--color-neutral-100);
  --pvc-color-text-muted: var(--color-neutral-400);
  --pvc-color-accent: var(--color-primary-400);
  --pvc-color-accent-strong: var(--color-primary-300);
  --pvc-color-accent-solid: var(--color-primary-700);
  --pvc-color-accent-solid-hover: var(--color-primary-600);
  --pvc-color-focus: var(--color-primary-400);
}
```

### Reading the stack

| Layer | Token | Role |
|-------|-------|------|
| Canvas | `--pvc-color-surface` | Page background, default panel fill |
| Recess | `--pvc-color-surface-muted` | Field groups, secondary regions |
| Lift | `--pvc-color-surface-raised` | Subtle elevation within dark UI (mix, not shadow) |
| Edge | `--pvc-color-border` | Standard dividers and control outlines |
| Emphasis edge | `--pvc-color-border-strong` | Buttons, emphasized frames |

Avoid `neutral-950` as the **default large-surface background** for application chrome.

## Dense Data Exception

`Pathogen::DataGridComponent` may use `--pvc-data-grid-body-bg: var(--color-neutral-950)` **inside the grid frame** to increase row contrast for tabular data. This is intentional and local to the grid — not permission to use `neutral-950` for page shells, sidebars, or preview wrappers.

When adding new dense data surfaces, follow the same rule: deeper inset within a bordered frame, not a darker application canvas.

## Focus In Dark Mode

Default: `--pvc-color-focus` (`primary-400` in dark mode).

Host applications (IRIDA) may map focus to white for brand reasons. If overriding, preserve:

- `focus-visible` only (not mouse click rings).
- 2px outline minimum with offset.
- Distinction from selected and hover states.

Converge new components on `--pvc-color-focus` rather than hard-coded black/white outlines.

## Component Checklist

Verify in dark mode:

- [ ] Data grid — header, body, row hover, selection, sticky columns
- [ ] Forms — labels, inputs, validation, disabled
- [ ] Buttons — all tone/emphasis pairs, disabled, `aria-disabled`
- [ ] Tabs — selected indicator, hover, keyboard focus
- [ ] Tooltips and overlays — contrast on `neutral-950` fill
- [ ] Typography — default, muted, inverse variants
- [ ] Code blocks and `CopyableValue`
- [ ] Preview backgrounds — neutral product shell, not gradient docs chrome

## What Not To Do

- Decorative gradients to “warm up” dark UI.
- Glow, blur, or oversized colour blocks to fix contrast.
- Removing borders because “dark mode is flat enough.”
- Different radius or spacing logic than light mode without workflow reason.
